cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.SE 

The paper discusses safety mechanisms for Deep Neural Networks (DNNs) used in highly automated driving (HAD) systems. This involves perception functions, which are related to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the need for a framework to describe and mitigate DNN insufficiencies, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the evaluation of these safety mechanisms, which involves software engineering (cs.SE) and robotics (cs.RO).
